28/12/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- A meeting between Serbian Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica and UNMIK chief Soren Jessen-Petersen will take place on 17 January in Belgrade, according to an aide to Kostunica, Aleksandar Simic. He told reporters Monday (27 December) that the talks would focus on issues related to Kosovo's decentralisation and minorities. 
In other news Monday, Serbian President Boris Tadic's office announced that a private company has donated 16,000 euros to settle the electricity bills of three Serb villages in central Kosovo. The Kosovo Energy Corporation is expected to restore power to the area shortly. (Danas, Beta - 28/12/04; B92, FoNet, Tanjug - 27/12/04)
